  "text": "## Kafka Streams DSL to Processor API Migration Analysis\n\nThe Apache Kafka Streams library (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489) provides a two-level abstraction for stream processing: the high-level Kafka Streams DSL and the low-level Processor API.\n\n### Key DSL Operations and Their Processor API Equivalents\n\n**1. Filter Operation**\n- **DSL Interface**: `KStream.filter(Predicate<K, V>)` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/KStream.java:76)\n- **DSL Implementation**: `KStreamImpl.filter()` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamImpl.java:146-172)\n- **Processor API Adapter**: `KStreamFilter<K, V>` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamFilter.java:25)\n- **Processor API Interface Used**: `FixedKeyProcessorSupplier<K, V, V>` which produces `FixedKeyProcessor<K, V, V>`\n- **Implementation Detail**: KStreamFilter extends `ContextualFixedKeyProcessor` and uses the `FixedKeyRecord` type with forward() method to pass through filtered records\n\n**2. Map Operation**\n- **DSL Interface**: `KStream.map(KeyValueMapper<K, V, KeyValue<K', V'>>)` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/KStream.java:250)\n- **DSL Implementation**: `KStreamImpl.map()` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamImpl.java:283-311)\n- **Processor API Adapter**: `KStreamMap<KIn, VIn, KOut, VOut>` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamMap.java:28)\n- **Processor API Interface Used**: `ProcessorSupplier<KIn, VIn, KOut, VOut>` which produces `Processor<KIn, VIn, KOut, VOut>`\n- **Implementation Detail**: KStreamMap extends `ContextualProcessor` and transforms both key and value using the mapper, supporting key-changing operations\n\n**3. GroupBy Operation**\n- **DSL Interface**: `KStream.groupBy(KeyValueMapper<K, V, K'>, Grouped<K', V>)` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/KStream.java:674-683)\n- **DSL Implementation**: `KStreamImpl.groupBy()` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamImpl.java:693-716)\n- **Processor API Adapter**: Uses `KStreamMap` internally via `internalSelectKey()` to extract the new grouping key\n- **Processor API Interface Used**: `ProcessorSupplier<K, V, K', V>` for key selection, then produces `KGroupedStreamImpl`\n- **Implementation Detail**: groupBy internally calls internalSelectKey which uses KStreamMap to select the new key, enabling key-based repartitioning\n\n**4. FlatMap Operation**\n- **DSL Interface**: `KStream.flatMap(KeyValueMapper<K, V, Iterable<KeyValue<K', V'>>>)` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/KStream.java:306)\n- **DSL Implementation**: `KStreamImpl.flatMap()` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamImpl.java:314-335)\n- **Processor API Adapter**: `KStreamFlatMap<KIn, VIn, KOut, VOut>` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamFlatMap.java:28)\n- **Processor API Interface Used**: `ProcessorSupplier<KIn, VIn, KOut, VOut>` which produces `Processor<KIn, VIn, KOut, VOut>`\n- **Implementation Detail**: KStreamFlatMap extends `ContextualProcessor` and forwards multiple records per input record using forward() in a loop\n\n**5. MapValues Operation**\n- **DSL Interface**: `KStream.mapValues(ValueMapper<V, V'>)` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/KStream.java:188)\n- **DSL Implementation**: `KStreamImpl.mapValues()` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamImpl.java:241-280)\n- **Processor API Adapter**: `KStreamMapValues<KIn, VIn, VOut>` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamMapValues.java:25)\n- **Processor API Interface Used**: `FixedKeyProcessorSupplier<KIn, VIn, VOut>` which produces `FixedKeyProcessor<KIn, VIn, VOut>`\n- **Implementation Detail**: KStreamMapValues extends `ContextualFixedKeyProcessor` and preserves keys while transforming values only\n\n**6. FlatMapValues Operation**\n- **DSL Interface**: `KStream.flatMapValues(ValueMapper<V, Iterable<V'>>)` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/KStream.java:338)\n- **DSL Implementation**: `KStreamImpl.flatMapValues()` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamImpl.java:338-377)\n- **Processor API Adapter**: `KStreamFlatMapValues<KIn, VIn, VOut>` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamFlatMapValues.java:25)\n- **Processor API Interface Used**: `FixedKeyProcessorSupplier<KIn, VIn, VOut>` which produces `FixedKeyProcessor<KIn, VIn, VOut>`\n- **Implementation Detail**: KStreamFlatMapValues extends `ContextualFixedKeyProcessor` and forwards multiple value records with the same key\n\n**7. Peek Operation**\n- **DSL Interface**: `KStream.peek(ForeachAction<K, V>)` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/KStream.java:429)\n- **DSL Implementation**: `KStreamImpl.peek()` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamImpl.java:414-440)\n- **Processor API Adapter**: `KStreamPeek<K, V>` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamPeek.java:25)\n- **Processor API Interface Used**: `FixedKeyProcessorSupplier<K, V, V>` which produces `FixedKeyProcessor<K, V, V>`\n- **Implementation Detail**: KStreamPeek extends `ContextualFixedKeyProcessor` and executes the side effect action while passing through unchanged records\n\n**8. Foreach Operation**\n- **DSL Interface**: `KStream.foreach(ForeachAction<K, V>)` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/KStream.java:404)\n- **DSL Implementation**: `KStreamImpl.foreach()` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamImpl.java:394-411)\n- **Processor API Adapter**: `ForeachProcessor<K, V>` (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/ForeachProcessor.java)\n- **Processor API Interface Used**: `ProcessorSupplier<K, V, Void, Void>` which produces `Processor<K, V, Void, Void>`\n- **Implementation Detail**: Terminal operation that executes an action without forwarding records\n\n### Core Processor API Interfaces\n\n**1. Processor Interface** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/api/Processor.java:34)\n- Generic interface with type parameters: `<KIn, VIn, KOut, VOut>`\n- Allows transformation of both keys and values\n- Methods: `init(ProcessorContext)`, `process(Record)`, `close()`\n- Used for key-changing operations (map, flatMap)\n\n**2. FixedKeyProcessor Interface** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/api/FixedKeyProcessor.java:33)\n- Generic interface with type parameters: `<KIn, VIn, VOut>`\n- Restricts key transformation; output keys match input keys\n- Methods: `init(FixedKeyProcessorContext)`, `process(FixedKeyRecord)`, `close()`\n- Used for value-only transformations (filter, mapValues, flatMapValues, peek)\n\n**3. ProcessorSupplier Interface** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/api/ProcessorSupplier.java)\n- Factory pattern interface for creating Processor instances\n- Allows custom initialization and reuse of Processor objects\n- Returns new Processor instances via `get()` method\n\n**4. FixedKeyProcessorSupplier Interface** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/api/FixedKeyProcessorSupplier.java)\n- Factory pattern interface for creating FixedKeyProcessor instances\n- Similar to ProcessorSupplier but for FixedKeyProcessor\n\n### Bridge Mechanism: process() and processValues() Methods\n\nThe DSL provides explicit bridge methods to the Processor API:\n\n**process() Method** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/KStream.java:1550-1564)\n- Accepts a `ProcessorSupplier<K, V, KOut, VOut>`\n- Allows custom Processor implementation with full control\n- Supports key-changing operations with potential repartitioning\n- Use case: Custom state store management, complex transformations\n\n**processValues() Method** (streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/KStream.java:1580-1594)\n- Accepts a `FixedKeyProcessorSupplier<K, V, VOut>`\n- Restricts to FixedKeyProcessor, preserving key co-location\n- No repartitioning needed; efficient for value-only operations\n- Use case: Custom state store management without key changes\n\n### Architecture Pattern\n\nThe DSL-to-Processor API migration follows a consistent pattern:\n\n1. **DSL Method** (e.g., `KStream.map()`) defines the public API\n2. **Implementation Class** (e.g., `KStreamImpl.map()`) orchestrates the operation\n3. **Adapter Class** (e.g., `KStreamMap`) implements `ProcessorSupplier` or `FixedKeyProcessorSupplier`\n4. **Processor Class** (inner class) extends `ContextualProcessor` or `ContextualFixedKeyProcessor` and implements `process(Record)`\n5. **Context Usage** The processor uses `context().forward()` to emit records downstream\n\nThis design allows teams migrating to the Processor API to:\n- Understand how DSL operations work internally\n- Implement custom processors with state store access\n- Maintain similar semantics to DSL operations\n- Access ProcessorContext features (scheduling, punctuation, state stores)\n\n### Key Implementation Files for Migration Reference\n\n- **DSL Interfaces**: KStream.java, KTable.java define all high-level operations\n- **DSL Implementations**: KStreamImpl.java orchestrates DSL operations\n- **Adapter Classes**: KStreamMap.java, KStreamFilter.java, etc., show how to adapt DSL operations to Processor API\n- **Processor API Core**: Processor.java, FixedKeyProcessor.java define the low-level abstraction\n- **Context Interfaces**: ProcessorContext.java, FixedKeyProcessorContext.java provide state store and runtime access\n- **Record Types**: Record.java, FixedKeyRecord.java define the data flow between processors"
